The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4:10 p.m.  Lima  time.  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  rose for the first time this week,
gaining 0.8 percent to 22,839.18. The  MSCI (MXPECAPD)  All Peru Capped Index
climbed 0.2 percent to 2,854.39.  Panoro Minerals Ltd. (PML)  , a Canadian copper and gold
exploration company, advanced 3.9 percent to 79 cents after
copper rebounded from a two-week low in  New York .  Sociedad Minera Cerro Verde SA (CVERDEC1)  (CVERDEC1 PE), a unit of
Freeport-McMoRan Copper & Gold Inc., rose 3 percent to $41.  Empresa Agroindustrial Pomalca SA (POM\C)  (POMALCC1 PE), a sugar
producer, gained 3.5 percent to 59 centimos, the biggest one-day
gain since Feb. 8, after the government disclosed plans to sell
its remaining shares, said Arlen Lahura, a trader at Lima-based
brokerage Coril SAB.  Credicorp Ltd. (BAP)  , Peruâ€™s largest financial-services
company, climbed 1.8 percent to $126.27 after U.S. stocks rose,
said Estefany Castillo, an analyst at Scotiabank Peru.  To contact the reporter on this story:
